Work Contribution Tracking
1. GitHub Issues: (Harout & Hossam)
- Create an issue for each task and assign it to the respective team members.
- Each issue must include:
  - Title: [Task name]
  - Description: [Detailed description]
  - Labels: [Tags like 'bug,' 'enhancement,' 'core feature']
  - Milestone: [Sprint milestone]

2. GitHub Pull Requests: (Mohammed & Muaaz)
- Each team member submits a pull request for their assigned tasks.
- PRs must reference related issue numbers (e.g., Fixes #12).
- Assign reviewers for each PR.

3. Progress Updates:
- Weekly team meetings to update progress and blockers.
- Update a shared GitHub wiki page with:
  - Completed tasks
  - Pending tasks
  - Blockers or issues faced.
_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Checklist for Full Marks
- [/ ] Tasks assigned to all 8 members with clear deadlines.
- [ ] Each team member has at least one GitHub issue assigned to them.
- [ ] Contributions are visible in GitHub commits and pull requests.
- [ ] Equal distribution of tasks among all members.
- [ ] GitHub wiki page updated weekly with progress and blockers.
